        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the best GBP analytics tool in 2026?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>It depends on what you need. For action — analytics plus auto-posts that move the numbers — theStacc ($49/mo Local SEO). For pure geo-grid rank tracking, Local Falcon ($24.99/mo). For an audit-style local dashboard, BrightLocal ($39/mo). For free baseline data, the native GBP Insights tab inside your Profile dashboard.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is the free Google Business Profile Insights tab enough?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For 1 location and basic reporting, yes — GBP Insights shows impressions, clicks, direction requests, and calls for the past 6 months. The gaps: no geo-grid rank tracking, no review sentiment over time, no competitor benchmarking, and no historical data beyond 6 months. Most operators bolt on Local Falcon (geo-grid) or BrightLocal (audit) to fill those gaps.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is a geo-grid in GBP analytics?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A geo-grid scan ranks your Google Business Profile from dozens of points across a map around your location — usually a 7x7 or 11x11 grid. It tells you where on the map your profile shows up in the local pack and where you don't. Local Falcon and Local Viking pioneered the format, and BrightLocal and Localo now bundle it.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do I need an agency-grade tool like BrightLocal as a single business?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Not for 1 location. BrightLocal and Whitespark shine at 5+ locations or when you need audit-style PDFs for clients. A single operator gets more value from native GBP Insights + Local Falcon ($24.99/mo) plus a done-for-you content tool like theStacc to act on the data.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How often should I check GBP analytics?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Weekly for direction requests, calls, and review velocity. Monthly for geo-grid rank shifts and category impressions. Most operators waste hours logging in daily — set a weekly recurring review of 4 metrics: calls, directions, photo views, and average map rank for your top 3 keywords.</p></div></div>
